41 SECTION 4. G.S. 20-81.12 is amended by adding the following new subsections to
42 read:
43 "() Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority. – The Division shall transfer quarterly the money in the
44 Collegiate and Cultural Attraction Plate Account derived from the sale of the Alpha Kappa Alpha
45 Sorority plates to the Alpha Kappa Alpha Educational Advancement Foundation, Inc.
46 () Delta Sigma Theta Sorority. – The Division shall transfer quarterly the money in the
47 Collegiate and Cultural Attraction Plate Account derived from the sale of the Delta Sigma Theta
48 Sorority plates to the Delta Research and Educational Foundation.
49 () Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity. – The Division shall transfer quarterly the money in the
50 Collegiate and Cultural Attraction Plate Account derived from the sale of the Kappa Alpha Psi
51 Fraternity plates to the Kappa Alpha Psi Foundation.
Page 2 DRH10199-NEf-70

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 () Phi Beta Sigma Fraternity. – The Division shall transfer quarterly the money in the
2 Collegiate and Cultural Attraction Plate Account derived from the sale of the Phi Beta Sigma
3 Fraternity plates to the PBS Impact Foundation.
4 () Sigma Gamma Rho Sorority. – The Division shall transfer quarterly the money in the
5 Collegiate and Cultural Attraction Plate Account derived from the sale of the Sigma Gamma Rho
6 Sorority plates to the Sigma Gamma Rho Sorority National Education Fund, Inc."
7 SECTION 5. The Revisor of Statutes is authorized to alphabetize, number, and
8 renumber the special registration plates listed in G.S. 20-79.4(b) and G.S. 20-81.12 to ensure that
9 all the special registration plates are listed in alphabetical order and numbered accordingly.
10 SECTION 6. This act is effective when it becomes law.
